{{short description|A ridge in the eastern Caribbean Sea west of the Lesser Antilles Volcanic Arc}}
{{coord|14|-63.5|format=dms|display=title}}

The '''Aves Ridge''' is a ridge in the eastern [[Caribbean Sea]]. It runs in a north-south direction, approximately 250 km west of the [[Lesser Antilles Volcanic Arc]]. It is mostly under water, but it reaches the surface in the north as [[Aves Island]] and in the south as [[Blanquilla Island]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Isla Blanquilla, Venezuela: Image of the Day|publisher=NASA|url=http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=8252|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090425234227/http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=8252|archivedate=25 April 2009|deadurl=no|date=26 November 2007}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|author=James, Keith L.|title=The Caribbean Ocean Plateau – an overview, and a different understanding|pages=2,4|url=http://www.mantleplumes.org/WebDocuments/CaribbeanPlateau.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003122036/http://www.mantleplumes.org/WebDocuments/CaribbeanPlateau.pdf|archivedate=3 October 2008|deadurl=no}}</ref> Most geologists believe that the Aves Ridge originated as an [[volcanic arc]] which is now extinct, though its width poses a problem<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deepseadrilling.org/78a/volume/dsdp78a_02.pdf |title=Geophysics and the Structure of the Lesser Antilles Forearc |last1= Westbrook|first1= G.K|last2=Biju-Duval|first2=B.|last3=Mascle|first3=A.|date=September 20, 1983 |website= Deep Sea Drilling Project |publisher= |access-date=22 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref>; the date of its origin is generally placed in the [[Cretaceous]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mantleplumes.org/WebDocuments/CaribbeanPlateau.pdf |title=The Caribbean Ocean Plateau – an overview, and a different understanding |last=James |first=Keith H. |date=2007 |website=<nowiki>MantlePlumes.org</nowiki> |publisher= |access-date= 22 September 2017 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |editor1-last=Bally |editor1-first=Albert W.|editor2-last=Palmer |editor2-first=Allison R. |date= 1989 |title=Geology of North America—An Overview |url= https://books.google.co.nz/books?id=DyF3BQAAQBAJ |location=Boulder, Colorado |publisher= [[Geological Society of America]] |page=314 |isbn= 9780813754451 |author-link= }}</ref>

