__NOTOC__ {{Use Australian English|date=July 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date= July 2015}} {{Infobox Australian place | type = protected | name = Bremer Marine Park | state = au | iucn_category = | image = | caption = | image_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|34|45|S|119|50|E|scale:1000000|display=inline,title}} | relief = yes | pushpin_label_position = top | map_alt = | nearest_town_or_city = [[Bremer Bay, Western Australia|Bremer Bay]] | area = 4472 | area_footnotes = <ref name="South-west-MP">{{cite book |last1=[[Director of National Parks]] |title=South-west Marine Parks Network Management Plan 2018 |date=2018 |publisher=Director of National Parks |location=Canberra |isbn=978-0-9876152-4-4 |url=https://parksaustralia.gov.au/marine/pub/plans/south-west-management-plan-2018.pdf |accessdate=10 July 2018|pages=112-114}}</ref> | established = 14 December 2013 | established_footnotes = <ref name="South-west-MP"/> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_footnotes = | managing_authorities = [[Director of National Parks]]<ref name="South-west-MP"/> | url = https://parksaustralia.gov.au/marine/parks/south-west/bremer/ }} The '''Bremer Marine Park''' (formerly '''Bremer Commonwealth Marine Reserve''') is a 4472&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> [[marine protected area]], with a depth range of about 15–5000&nbsp;m, lying in the [[Southern Ocean]] off the southern coast of [[Western Australia]] about 50&nbsp;km south-east of the town of [[Bremer Bay]]. An area of 284&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>, comprising the northernmost section adjoining Western Australia’s coastal waters, has been zoned as a marine [[national park]] ([[IUCN protected area categories|IUCN Category II]]), with the remainder as multiple use or special purpose zones (IUCN Category VI).<ref name=doe/>
It was gazetted in 14 December 2013 and was renamed on 11 October 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=Environment Protection and Biodiversity Conservation Amendment (Commonwealth Marine Reserves Renaming) Proclamation 2017 |url=https://www.legislation.gov.au/Details/F2017L01337 |website=Federal Register of Legislation |publisher=Australian Government |accessdate=5 July 2018 |date=11 October 2017}}</ref><ref name="South-west-MP"/>
==Fauna== The marine park provides important seasonal calving habitat for [[southern right whale]]s as well as supporting migrating [[humpback whale]]s. It is a foraging area for [[Australian sea lion]]s, [[Indian yellow-nosed albatross]]es, [[flesh-footed shearwater]]s, [[soft-plumaged petrel]]s and [[great white shark]]s. It also encompasses Bremer Canyon, a [[submarine canyon]] known as a [[biodiversity hotspot]] supporting seasonal aggregations of [[sperm whale|sperm]] and [[killer whale]]s.<ref name=doe>{{cite web |url= http://www.environment.gov.au/topics/marine/marine-reserves/south-west/bremer |title= Bremer Commonwealth Marine Reserve |accessdate=2014-04-21 |work= South-west Commonwealth marine Reserves Network |first= |last= |publisher=Department of the Environment, Australia |date= }}</ref>
