{{other uses|Mirny (disambiguation)}} {|{{Infobox ship begin}} {{Infobox ship image |Ship image=RR5415-0009R.gif |Ship image size=270px |Ship caption=''Mirny'' and its Captain [[Mikhail Lazarev]] on a commemorative coin of the [[Bank of Russia]] }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship country=[[Russian Empire]] |Ship flag= |Ship name=''Mirny'' |Ship namesake=[[Peace]]ful |url= |accessdate= |Ship ordered= |Ship builder=*[[Mikhail Lazarev]] (oversaw refit of the original ship ''Ladoga''), *Olonetskaya Shipyards, *[[Lodeynoye Pole]] |Ship original cost= |Ship laid down=1818 |Ship launched=1819 |Ship sponsor= |Ship christened=''Ladoga'' |Ship maiden voyage=1819 |Ship renamed=''Mirny'' |Ship reclassified= |Ship homeport=[[Kronshtadt]] |Ship nickname= |Ship status= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Hide header= |Header caption= |Ship type=24-gun [[sloop-of-war]] |Ship tonnage= |Ship displacement=530 tonnes<ref name=sailhistory/> |Ship tons burthen= |Ship length={{convert|36.6|m|abbr=on|1}}<ref name=sailhistory/> |Ship beam={{convert|9.15|m|abbr=on|1}} <ref name=sailhistory/> |Ship height= |Ship draft= |Ship hold depth={{convert|4.6|m|abbr=on|1}}<ref name=sailhistory/> |Ship decks= |Ship sail plan=[[Full-rigged ship]] |Ship speed= {{convert|10|kn|km/h|abbr=on|lk=in}}<ref name=sailhistory/> |Ship boats= |Ship complement=72<ref name=sailhistory/> |Ship armament=*6 × 120 mm [[carronade]] *14 × 76 mm pounders<ref name=sailhistory/> }} |}
'''''Mirny''''' was a 20-gun [[sloop-of-war]] of the [[Imperial Russian Navy]], the second ship of the First Russian Antarctic Expedition in 1819—1821, during which [[Fabian Gottlieb von Bellingshausen]] (commander of the lead ship ''[[Vostok (sloop-of-war)|Vostok]]'') and [[Mikhail Lazarev]] (commanding ''Mirny'') [[circumnavigation|circumnavigated]] the globe, discovered the continent of [[Antarctica]] and twice circumnavigated it, and discovered a number of islands and archipelagos in the [[Southern Ocean]] and the [[Pacific]].<ref name=sailhistory>[http://sailhistory.ru/index.php?option=content&id=198&task=view Шлюп "Мирный"] at sailhistory.ru {{ru icon}}</ref>
== History == [[File:Lazarevpetrovich.jpg|thumb|180px|left|[[Mikhail Lazarev]], captain of ''Mirny''.]] ''Mirny'' was under construction in 1818 at Olonetskaya Shipyards, [[Lodeynoye Pole]]. It was initially named ''Ladoga'' (after [[Lake Ladoga]]), but when a new ship became needed for an Antarctic expedition, the decision was taken not to build a completely new one, but to refit ''Ladoga''. It was reconstructed under surveillance of its future commander Mikhail Lazarev.<ref name=sailhistory/>
On {{OldStyleDate|14 July|1819|3 July}} ''Vostok'' under the captaincy of [[Commander]] Fabian Gottlieb von Bellingshausen, the leader of the expedition, alongside ''Mirny'' under the command of [[Lieutenant Commander]] Mikhail Lazarev left [[Kronshtadt]] and on {{OldStyleDate|28 January|1820|16 January}} reached the shore of [[Antarctica]], which was sighted for the first time in history. After repair in [[Sydney]] in [[Australia]], the expedition explored the tropical parts of the Pacific, and on {{OldStyleDate|12 November|1820|31 October}} again turned to Antarctica. On {{OldStyleDate|22 January|1821|10 January}} the sloops reached the southernmost point of their voyage at 69° 53' S and 92° 19' W. On {{OldStyleDate|5 August|1821|24 July}} they returned to Kronshtadt.<ref name=sailhistory/>
In 751 days they covered 49&nbsp;723 miles (circa 92&nbsp;300&nbsp;km). Apart from the discovery of the world's sixth continent, [[Antarctica]], 29 islands were mapped and complex oceanographic works carried out. A medal was issued by the [[Russian Admiralty]] to commemorate the expedition.<ref name=sailhistory/>
== Named in honor == [[File:Platinum coin5318-0006R.gif|thumb|180px|left|''Vostok'' (left) and ''Mirny'' (right) during the First Russian Antarctic Expedition on a coin of the [[Bank of Russia]]]] * [[List of geological features on Mercury|Mirny Rupes]], a mountain chain on planet [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]].<ref>[http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/SearchResults?target=MERCURY&featureType=Rupes%2C%20rup%C4%93s Batson R.M., Russell J.F. (1994), Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature, United States Geological Survey Bulletin 2129] planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov</ref> * [[Mirny Peak]], a prominent [[summit (topography)|peak]], 750 m, 4 nautical miles (7&nbsp;km) northeast of [[Enigma Peak]] in the north part of [[Rothschild Island]], presumably first seen from a distance in 1821 by the First Russian Antarctic Expedition.<ref>[http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=129:3:1348295785774950::NO::P3_ANTAR_ID,P3_TITLE:10057%2CMirnyy%20Peak Mirnyy Peak] [[Geographic Names Information System]]</ref> * [[Mirny Station]], a Russian Antarctic research station on the coast of the [[Davis Sea]], established on February 13, 1956 by the [[1st Soviet Antarctic Expedition]].<ref>[http://www.vokrugsveta.ru/telegraph/history/505/ Полвека в глубине Антарктиды] [[Vokrug Sveta]] {{ru icon}}</ref> * [[Mirny Peninsula]], on which Mirny Station is located.<ref>[http://www.aari.aq/stations/mir/mir_en.html Mirny Observatory] [[AARI]]</ref>
== References == {{reflist}} * Морской энциклопедический словарь. Л.: Судостроение, 1991. {{ISBN|5-7355-0280-8}} {{ru icon}} * [http://hobbyport.ru/ships/mirny.htm Mirny, with model scheme] at hobbyport.ru {{ru icon}}
