{{Infobox airport | name = Niue International Airport | nativename = | nativename-a = | nativename-r = | image = NiueInternationalAirport.jpg | image-width = 200 | caption = Entrance to Niue International Airport | IATA = IUE | ICAO = NIUE | pushpin_map = Niue | pushpin_map_caption = Location of airport in Niue | pushpin_label = IUE | pushpin_label_position = bottom | type = Public | owner = | operator = | city-served = | location = Niue | elevation-f = 209 | elevation-m = 64 | coordinates = {{Coord|19|04|44|S|169|55|33|W|type:airport_region:NU|display=inline,title}} | website = | metric-elev = | metric-rwy = | r1-number = 10/28 | r1-length-f = 7,660 | r1-length-m = 2,335 | r1-surface = [[Asphalt]] | stat-year = | stat1-header = | stat1-data = | stat2-header = | stat2-data = | footnotes = }}
'''Niue International Airport''' {{airport codes|IUE|NIUE}}, also known as '''Hanan International Airport''', is an international airport serving the island nation of [[Niue]]. It is located near the town of [[Alofi]] and currently only serves [[Air New Zealand]], flying to and from [[Auckland]] twice a week, departing Auckland on Tuesdays and Saturdays, and departing Niue on Mondays and Fridays.{{efn|group=notes|Because New Zealand and Niue are on opposite sides of the [[International Date Line]], the Tuesday morning flight from Auckland arrives in Niue on Monday, then departs a few hours later, arriving back in Auckland on Tuesday evening. Similarly, the Saturday morning flight from Auckland arrives in Niue on Friday, then departs a few hours later, arriving back in Auckland on Saturday evening.}}
It was opened in December 1970 at which time it was serviced by [[Fokker F.27 Friendship]] aircraft. For a period in the 1990s, Niue International Airport served as the base of [[Niue Airlines]].
