'''Olympia''' was a 5,000-capacity music venue located in the [[São Paulo]], [[Brazil]]. It was open from 1988 until 2006. A few of the notable artists that performed at Olympia include [[David Bowie]], [[Cyndi Lauper]], [[Uriah Heep (band)|Uriah Heep]], [[Eric Clapton]], [[Deep Purple]], [[Jethro Tull (band)|Jethro Tull]], [[Black Sabbath]], [[Pantera]] and [[Sting (musician)|Sting]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.setlist.fm/venue/olympia-sao-paulo-brazil-3bd624d0.html |title=Olympia, São Paulo, Brazil Concert Setlists |publisher=setlist.fm |date= |accessdate=2018-08-10}}</ref>

