{{Infobox mountain | name = Pico Teneriffe | photo = | elevation_m = 100 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = | prominence_ref = | map =Barbados | map_caption = | map_size = | label_position = | location = [[Saint Peter, Barbados|Saint Peter]], [[Barbados]] | range = | coordinates = {{coord|13.294425|-59.572791|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | topo = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
The '''Pico Teneriffe''', is a rocky cape on the northeast coast of the island of [[Barbados]], in the [[Saint Peter, Barbados|Parish of Saint Peter]].<ref name="barbadospocketguide">{{cite web|url=http://www.barbadospocketguide.com/barbados-attractions/beaches-and-bays/north-coast-beaches/pico-teneriffe.html|publisher=barbadospocketguide.com|title=Pico Teneriffe - Barbados Pocket Guide|accessdate=2016-11-27}}</ref>
It is a coral cliff in the shape of a pinnacle that does not reach 100 meters in height, named after the fact that the island of [[Tenerife]] in [[Spain]] is the first land east of Barbados, according to the inhabitants of the place. The presence in the place of people arrived from the [[Canary Islands]] in the time of the colonization of Barbados is not ruled out, but unlikely.<ref name="barbadospocketguide"/><ref name="diariodeavisos">{{cite web|url=http://www.diariodeavisos.com/2015/11/tenerife-desde-antipodas-hasta-luna/|publisher=diariodeavisos.com|title=Tenerife: desde las antípodas hasta la Luna &#124; Diario de Avisos|accessdate=2016-11-27}}</ref>
